&lt;p&gt;Join us on our mission to empower more people to find their way home by breaking barriers to entry, making the right connections, and building confidence through expert guidance.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;p&gt;Realtor.com is a two-sided platform helping match the consumers on our site and apps to our paying customers. The Data Science &amp;amp; Analytics team at Realtor.com provides trusted data and insights to optimize every aspect of consumer/customer experience and to drive the company’s commercial performance.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Avail Realtor.com&amp;nbsp;is a fast-growing platform transforming how independent landlords and tenants manage the rental experience. Built with the spirit of a startup and backed by the scale and stability of a leading digital real estate company, Avail provides a complete suite of tools, resources, and education to help landlords manage their properties with confidence and professionalism. As part of the Avail team, you’ll have the opportunity to make a meaningful impact – shaping the future of this rapidly expanding brand and helping to reimagine the rental industry for millions across the U.S..&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Role&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We&#39;re looking for an experienced &lt;em&gt;Senior Data Analyst&lt;/em&gt; with a strong background in business intelligence and strategic analytics to help shape the future of Avail. As a trusted partner to the Avail leadership team, you will be the vital link between complex data and pivotal business moves, striving to enable and empower data-driven decision making across the business.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In this role, you will analyze large and complex data sets, define and track business KPIs, build automated reporting solutions, conduct robust analyses, generate actionable insights, and deliver clear recommendations that inform critical decisions across strategy, product, marketing, and operations.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate is a detail-oriented analytics expert, a self-starter comfortable with ambiguity, and a team player who excels in cross-functional collaborations, with the ability to work in a fast-paced environment, and driven by a desire to make things better.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner closely with Avail business stakeholders to understand/clarify needs and requirements, and translate them into analytical problems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;If the required data is not available, work with the team to identify the right data sources, and build analytical data layers in collaboration with the data engineering partner.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Independently conduct end-to-end data analytical work from data collection, ETL, analysis, to the delivery of insights and recommendations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as Avail’s Business Intelligence expert and own KPI development, measurement, tracking, and reporting. Closely monitor KPIs and carry out deep-dive analysis to explain changes and trends, and surface areas of opportunities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and run regular business performance reporting, and actively contribute analytics-related content to business reviews and other reports.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build automated reports and dashboards using tools such as Tableau, Mixpanel, etc.&lt;/li&gt;

